# Supabase API Keys — New System & PostgREST Error Codes

---

## ⚠️ API Key Breaking Change — November 2025

**New Supabase projects created after November 2025 NO LONGER have anon or service_role keys.**

| | Legacy (pre-Nov 2025) | New (post-Nov 2025) |
|---|---|---|
| Public key name | `anon` | `sb_publishable_...` |
| Secret key name | `service_role` | `sb_secret_...` |
| Env var (public) | `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` |
| Env var (secret) | `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` |
| Edge Function var | `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | `SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` |
| Key is a JWT? | Yes — can use as Bearer token | **No** — cannot use as Bearer token |

**How to check which system your project uses:**
```
Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API
If you see "anon public" and "service_role" labels → legacy keys
If you see "Publishable" and "Secret" labels → new keys
```

---

## New Key System — What Each Key Does

### sb_publishable_ (replaces anon)
```
Safe to expose in browser code (NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix)
Used to identify your project to PostgREST and Storage
NOT a JWT — cannot be used as Authorization: Bearer token
Used in: apikey header, not Authorization header
Access level: whatever RLS policies allow for unauthenticated users
```

### sb_secret_ (replaces service_role)
```
NEVER expose in browser or client-side code
Bypasses ALL Row Level Security
Used in: server-side code, Edge Functions, admin operations
Store as server-only env var (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix)
```

