## Critical: Authorization Header Change

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG with new keys — sb_publishable_ is NOT a JWT
const response = await fetch(`${SUPABASE_URL}/rest/v1/products`, {
  headers: {
    'Authorization': `Bearer ${SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY}`,  // WRONG — not a JWT
    'apikey': SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY,
  }
})

// ✅ CORRECT with new keys — apikey header carries the publishable key
// Authorization header carries ONLY the user's session JWT (or omit for anon)
const response = await fetch(`${SUPABASE_URL}/rest/v1/products`, {
  headers: {
    'apikey': process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY!,
    'Authorization': `Bearer ${userSessionJWT}`,  // only when user is signed in
  }
})

// ✅ supabase-js handles this automatically — no manual header management needed
const { data } = await supabase.from('products').select()
// supabase-js sends the correct apikey and Authorization headers automatically
```

