## PostgREST Error Codes — Complete Reference

Every supabase-js error has a `code` field with a PGRST prefix. These are the most common:

| Code | When you see it | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `PGRST100` | Malformed filter or query syntax | Check `.eq()` / `.filter()` params — likely wrong operator or type mismatch |
| `PGRST102` | Badly formed range header | Check `.range(from, to)` values — from must be ≤ to |
| `PGRST106` | Schema not in `exposed schemas` | Dashboard → API → Exposed schemas → add schema. Or run `ALTER ROLE authenticator SET pgrst.db_schemas` |
| `PGRST116` | `.single()` returned multiple rows (or zero) | Use `.maybeSingle()` if 0-1 rows expected, `.single()` only if exactly 1 guaranteed |
| `PGRST200` | Relationship not found for embedded select | Check FK exists, check column names match exactly |
| `PGRST201` | Multiple relationships found — ambiguous | Disambiguate with explicit FK: `profiles!orders_user_id_fkey(...)` |
| `PGRST204` | No data returned (update/delete matched 0 rows) | Check your `.eq()` filter — row may not exist or RLS blocked it |
| `PGRST301` | JWT expired | User's session expired — call `supabase.auth.refreshSession()` or redirect to login |
| `PGRST302` | JWT invalid / malformed | Wrong key used as Bearer token — check createClient() uses correct key |
| `PGRST401` | No JWT provided but required | Missing Authorization header — user not logged in |
| `PGRST403` | Insufficient privileges (beyond RLS) | Missing GRANT on table — `GRANT SELECT ON table TO authenticated` |
| `PGRST409` | Unique constraint violation | Duplicate value on unique column — handle conflict or use `.upsert()` |
| `42501` | RLS policy violation (PostgreSQL code) | RLS blocked the operation — check policies for that table/operation |
| `23503` | Foreign key violation | Referenced row does not exist — check FK constraint |
| `23505` | Unique violation | Duplicate key — same as PGRST409 but from direct Postgres |

### Handling errors properly in supabase-js

```typescript
// Full response structure
const { data, error, count, status, statusText } = await supabase
  .from('orders')
  .select('*', { count: 'exact' })  // count requires explicit option
  .eq('user_id', userId)

// ❌ WRONG — data is null on error, not []
if (data.length === 0) { /* crashes if data is null */ }

// ✅ CORRECT — always check error first
if (error) {
  switch (error.code) {
    case 'PGRST116':
      // Multiple rows returned — change .single() to .maybeSingle()
      break
    case '42501':
      // RLS blocked — user doesn't have access
      return null
    case 'PGRST301':
      // JWT expired — refresh session
      await supabase.auth.refreshSession()
      break
    default:
      console.error(`Supabase error ${error.code}:`, error.message, error.details)
  }
  return null
}

// data is guaranteed non-null here
const orders = data ?? []
```
